WEBVTT

00:04.308 --> 00:06.876
<i>[eerie music]</i>

00:06.919 --> 00:08.660
I overheard you talking.

00:08.704 --> 00:10.053
You said there's way more
going on with these sinkholes

00:10.097 --> 00:11.185
than anyone knows.

00:11.228 --> 00:12.838
You're right.

00:12.882 --> 00:14.884
The next sinkhole will create
one of the largest tidal waves

00:14.927 --> 00:16.712
the world has ever seen.

00:16.755 --> 00:18.018
If it looks like
I've been compromised

00:18.061 --> 00:20.324
by the relationship we had--
- Had?

00:20.368 --> 00:22.500
Joseph, take the food,
all of it!

00:22.544 --> 00:24.198
<i>We want to go to the village
and take our food back.</i>

00:24.241 --> 00:25.590
There's going to
be a price to pay.

00:25.634 --> 00:27.853
- You came back just for me?
- Yes.

00:27.897 --> 00:30.378
- You shouldn't have done that.
- Veronica, wait.

00:30.421 --> 00:32.380
Several things
need to be accomplished,

00:32.423 --> 00:36.123
one of which is getting your
friends Josh and Riley back.

00:36.166 --> 00:38.647
Now go back
to the clearing and wait.

00:38.690 --> 00:40.692
- What am I waiting for?
- For Gavin.

00:40.736 --> 00:43.391
- You said Izzy was fine.
- Izzy is fine. She's here.

00:43.434 --> 00:45.306
- Izzy?
- Mom?

00:45.349 --> 00:48.135
<i>[swelling dramatic music]</i>

00:49.136 --> 00:52.052
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

00:52.095 --> 00:58.710
<i>♪</i>

00:58.754 --> 01:02.888
[inhales deeply]

01:02.932 --> 01:06.066
[groans softly]

01:06.109 --> 01:09.069
Have you been watching me
all night?

01:09.112 --> 01:10.766
No, not all night.

01:10.809 --> 01:11.810
Mm-hmm.

01:11.854 --> 01:13.856
Okay, yes.

01:13.899 --> 01:17.555
All night.
- [laughs]

01:17.599 --> 01:19.079
I know it's only
been a little while,

01:19.122 --> 01:22.517
but it feels like years.

01:22.560 --> 01:24.562
I was so afraid I had lost you.

01:24.606 --> 01:29.915
I never gave up hope, Mom,
and neither did Dad.

01:29.959 --> 01:34.790
<i>♪</i>

01:34.833 --> 01:37.227
Hey.

01:37.271 --> 01:43.364
<i>♪</i>

01:43.407 --> 01:44.756
I can't remember
the last time

01:44.800 --> 01:46.671
I saw you two
smile at each other.

01:46.715 --> 01:47.759
[both chuckle]

01:47.803 --> 01:50.719
It's nice.

01:50.762 --> 01:54.549
Crazy as it sounds,
I am glad we're here.

01:54.592 --> 01:56.594
I am too.

01:56.638 --> 02:00.903
Uh, but the thing is,
it's not safe here.

02:00.946 --> 02:02.426
Listen, I know you
don't always believe it,

02:02.470 --> 02:03.949
but I can handle myself.

02:03.993 --> 02:05.821
You don't understand
what it's like down here.

02:05.864 --> 02:08.606
Izzy, your mom's right.
It's dangerous.

02:08.650 --> 02:10.521
Which is why we're going
to get Josh back from '88

02:10.565 --> 02:13.524
and we are going to find
our way back home as a family.

02:13.568 --> 02:15.961
But Aldridge is the only one
who can help us get Josh back,

02:16.005 --> 02:18.964
so we have to find her.

02:19.008 --> 02:23.273
I'm going to go talk to the
others and figure out a plan.

02:23.317 --> 02:25.841
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

02:25.884 --> 02:28.148
<i>♪</i>

02:28.191 --> 02:31.716
[sizzling]

02:31.760 --> 02:33.196
You sure they're safe?

02:33.240 --> 02:34.893
- They're eggs.
- Mm-hmm.

02:39.028 --> 02:42.031
Mm-hmm?

02:42.074 --> 02:43.772
[clears throat]

02:43.815 --> 02:44.990
Mm-mm, mm-mm.

02:45.034 --> 02:46.383
- Lucas?
- [grunts]

02:46.427 --> 02:47.471
What's happening?
What do I do? What--

02:47.515 --> 02:50.170
- [gags]
- What do I--

02:50.213 --> 02:53.085
[snickers]

02:53.129 --> 02:55.305
- That's not funny!
- Ow.

02:55.349 --> 02:56.306
It was pretty funny.

02:56.350 --> 02:58.830
[laughs in disbelief]

03:01.137 --> 03:03.531
[wind whistling]

03:06.055 --> 03:07.970
Hey!

03:08.013 --> 03:09.580
Top of the morning.

03:09.624 --> 03:11.495
What were you doing
out there?

03:11.539 --> 03:14.324
I just found
a ginormous field of marijuana

03:14.368 --> 03:17.414
where Whole Foods used to be--
or will be.

03:17.458 --> 03:19.155
- Wow.
- Yeah.

03:19.199 --> 03:21.505
Did you, uh, find a cure
for your ankle as well?

03:21.549 --> 03:23.420
You're not limping.

03:23.464 --> 03:24.682
<i>[ominous music]</i>

03:24.726 --> 03:27.032
Weed--
must have dulled the pain.

03:27.076 --> 03:28.556
What the hell is
going on with you, man?

03:28.599 --> 03:30.079
Huh?

03:30.122 --> 03:32.037
You're hiding something.

03:32.081 --> 03:35.954
Wha--interesting theory,
but without a shred of truth.

03:35.998 --> 03:39.088
Anyhoo, enjoy your brekkie.

03:39.131 --> 03:41.046
Little foggy out here,
isn't it?

03:41.090 --> 03:43.135
That guy's the worst liar
I've ever met.

03:43.179 --> 03:45.225
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

03:45.268 --> 03:48.097
<i>♪</i>

03:48.140 --> 03:49.881
I'm gonna get some water.

03:49.925 --> 03:52.232
Okay.

03:52.275 --> 03:55.017
Wait!

03:55.060 --> 03:58.455
Veronica?

03:58.499 --> 04:01.066
I just want to know
why you've been avoiding me.

04:01.110 --> 04:02.285
Did I do something wrong?

04:02.329 --> 04:03.895
No, you didn't.

04:03.939 --> 04:06.594
So what is it?

04:06.637 --> 04:11.555
Veronica, I came here
to help you because I love you

04:11.599 --> 04:15.080
and want to have
a relationship.

04:15.124 --> 04:16.778
I'm sorry, I can't.

04:16.821 --> 04:21.522
<i>♪</i>

04:21.565 --> 04:24.742
Gavin, how was your
first night in the clearing?

04:24.786 --> 04:28.398
Not exactly the Ritz,
but it was okay.

04:28.442 --> 04:31.009
What are you making?
- It's a lookout post.

04:31.053 --> 04:32.968
It's good to have eyes on
and around the area,

04:33.011 --> 04:34.752
especially if the
Exiles come for us,

04:34.796 --> 04:37.712
not to mention Paara's people.

04:37.755 --> 04:39.191
What's going on with them?

04:39.235 --> 04:40.758
Lucas, Scott, and Veronica

04:40.802 --> 04:43.674
snuck into the village the
other night, stole some food.

04:43.718 --> 04:46.068
We warned them
how foolish it was.

04:46.111 --> 04:47.374
They wouldn't listen.

04:47.417 --> 04:49.376
The village finds out,
they could retaliate.

04:49.419 --> 04:51.029
Paara's not going
to hurt anyone here.

04:51.073 --> 04:52.466
She's a friend.

04:52.509 --> 04:54.511
Friends don't take your food
and leave you to starve.

04:54.555 --> 04:56.296
Okay, right now
the most important thing

04:56.339 --> 05:00.082
is we get to that building
and we find Aldridge, okay?

05:00.125 --> 05:02.650
Look, it's getting
pretty bad out there.

05:02.693 --> 05:05.783
I remember when fog
like this would roll in.

05:05.827 --> 05:09.309
Once it hits, you can't
see anything or anyone.

05:09.352 --> 05:10.571
We're going to lose visibility soon.

05:10.614 --> 05:14.314
We got to move.

05:14.357 --> 05:19.754
<i>♪</i>

05:19.797 --> 05:22.713
Uh, Gavin.
Hi, I'm Scott.

05:22.757 --> 05:25.412
You might've heard of me.
Josh's best friend?

05:25.455 --> 05:26.500
Or not?

05:26.543 --> 05:29.067
Not a good time, Scott.

05:29.111 --> 05:32.157
I promise you'll want
to hear this.

05:32.201 --> 05:33.985
Rebecca Aldridge
wants to see you.

05:34.029 --> 05:35.639
<i>♪</i>

05:35.683 --> 05:37.728
Where is she?
What did she say?

05:37.772 --> 05:39.339
She's waiting nearby.

05:39.382 --> 05:41.863
She needs to go with you to
the building to get Josh back.

05:41.906 --> 05:43.647
<i>[ominous music]</i>

05:43.691 --> 05:45.693
But no one else can come.

05:45.736 --> 05:47.695
- Why not?
- She didn't tell me why.

05:47.738 --> 05:49.261
But going to the building
is super dangerous,

05:49.305 --> 05:51.394
and she needs you to do it.

05:51.438 --> 05:53.701
Look, Gavin,
she says she can get Josh.

05:53.744 --> 05:56.834
Isn't that why you're here,
to bring your family back?

05:56.878 --> 05:59.228
- Okay, I got to talk to Eve.
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

05:59.271 --> 06:00.316
Aldridge was very clear.

06:00.360 --> 06:01.839
Eve cannot come
to the building.

06:01.883 --> 06:03.537
You can't tell her
anything about this.

06:03.580 --> 06:05.539
Too late.

06:05.582 --> 06:08.237
I'm going with you.
- Give us a minute, Scott.

06:08.280 --> 06:11.022
- Uh--
- Scott.

06:11.066 --> 06:13.503
Of course.

06:13.547 --> 06:15.679
<i>♪</i>

06:15.723 --> 06:18.813
Just let me talk
to Aldridge here out.

06:18.856 --> 06:20.945
I just don't want you out
there alone, not in this fog.

06:20.989 --> 06:22.947
Okay, and I don't want you
put in any more danger.

06:22.991 --> 06:24.819
It's the same way
you feel about Izzy.

06:24.862 --> 06:26.168
[sighs]

06:26.211 --> 06:27.865
If I have to go to this
building myself, I will.

06:27.909 --> 06:29.432
Let me go find out
what's really going on.

06:29.476 --> 06:31.521
I don't trust her.

06:31.565 --> 06:35.612
Okay.
Do you trust me?

06:35.656 --> 06:36.918
- Yes.
- Yeah?

06:36.961 --> 06:40.443
Okay.

06:40.487 --> 06:42.227
Let me do this.

06:42.271 --> 06:49.409
<i>♪</i>

06:56.938 --> 06:58.113
Yeah.

06:58.156 --> 06:59.375
<i>♪</i>

06:59.419 --> 07:00.507
[zipper zips]

07:00.550 --> 07:03.074
I'm going to bring
our son back.

07:03.118 --> 07:08.993
<i>♪</i>

07:09.037 --> 07:11.953
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

07:17.524 --> 07:19.264
Do you really think
you can charge it?

07:19.308 --> 07:22.877
Theoretically,
anything's possible.

07:22.920 --> 07:25.401
Look at this thing.

07:25.445 --> 07:27.447
It's a phone,
but it's also a camera.

07:27.490 --> 07:30.188
And a computer.

07:30.232 --> 07:32.626
- Oh, my head hurts.
- Just focus.

07:32.669 --> 07:33.931
We need to turn my phone on.

07:33.975 --> 07:36.412
It has all the photos
I took in 10,000 B.C.

07:36.456 --> 07:38.414
This is the only way
we can prove

07:38.458 --> 07:39.894
that there's more going on
with these sinkholes.

07:39.937 --> 07:41.809
We have to make
people believe.

07:41.852 --> 07:43.288
You said it yourself.

07:43.332 --> 07:44.551
Thousands of people are going
to die in the tidal wave

07:44.594 --> 07:46.814
when the next one happens,
including my dad.

07:46.857 --> 07:49.991
I understand.
Okay, here we go.

07:50.034 --> 07:51.558
I think I got it.

07:51.601 --> 07:52.559
<i>[phone chiming]</i>

07:52.602 --> 07:54.343
[gasps and laughs]

07:54.386 --> 07:56.780
You're a genius!
[chuckles in relief]

07:56.824 --> 07:59.217
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

07:59.261 --> 08:01.829
Classy.
- [chuckles]

08:01.872 --> 08:03.961
These are all the pictures
I took down there.

08:04.005 --> 08:07.443
Oh, my God,
this is unbelievable!

08:07.487 --> 08:09.271
We need to show this to the
head of my geology department

08:09.314 --> 08:11.578
at Caltech,
Dr. Caroline Clark.

08:11.621 --> 08:13.493
She's well renowned
in the field.

08:13.536 --> 08:17.671
We get her on board,
everyone else will follow.

08:17.714 --> 08:20.064
<i>♪</i>

08:20.108 --> 08:21.065
Shouldn't be a problem.

08:21.109 --> 08:22.980
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

08:23.024 --> 08:24.547
Okay, why the hesitation?

08:24.591 --> 08:27.115
Well, last time I presented
my sinkhole theory to her,

08:27.158 --> 08:28.943
she called it academic drivel,

08:28.986 --> 08:31.162
warned me to never
bring it up again.

08:31.206 --> 08:32.729
Great, so she thinks
you're a crackpot.

08:32.773 --> 08:35.471
Perhaps.
But she'll like you, Riley.

08:35.515 --> 08:37.429
You should talk to her for us.

08:37.473 --> 08:39.997
Come on.
We're running out of time.

08:40.041 --> 08:42.391
[blows air]
Okay.

08:42.434 --> 08:46.003
Aldridge is here and
Gavin went off on his own?

08:46.047 --> 08:49.137
Hey, my dad wouldn't have
done this unless he had to.

08:49.180 --> 08:51.400
I get it, Izzy.

08:51.443 --> 08:54.229
But this is my daughter
we're talking about.

08:54.272 --> 08:55.622
I'm going after them.

08:55.665 --> 08:57.101
Hold on.

08:57.145 --> 09:00.627
Look at this fog coming in.
You'd be walking blind.

09:00.670 --> 09:03.325
You know how dangerous it is
out there on a normal day.

09:03.368 --> 09:04.631
Imagine what it's like

09:04.674 --> 09:05.762
when you can't see
what's in front of you.

09:05.806 --> 09:08.156
Gavin's out there.

09:08.199 --> 09:10.332
And he'll be all right.

09:10.375 --> 09:11.986
Right now, we need
to round everybody up

09:12.029 --> 09:13.988
and hunker down
till this passes.

09:14.031 --> 09:15.511
Fine.

09:15.555 --> 09:18.819
But once this fog clears,
I'm going after them.

09:18.862 --> 09:25.869
<i>♪</i>

09:25.913 --> 09:27.828
How much further, Scott?

09:27.871 --> 09:31.832
Well, when I left Rebecca,
I <i>could</i> see where I was going.

09:31.875 --> 09:34.182
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

09:34.225 --> 09:35.531
- You're lost.
- [scoffs]

09:35.575 --> 09:38.882
Oh, I am so lost.
[sighs]

09:38.926 --> 09:42.059
[distant howling]

09:42.103 --> 09:44.235
Over here, over here.
Get down, get down, get down.

09:44.279 --> 09:47.238
[howling continuing]

09:47.282 --> 09:50.764
[breathing heavily]
Sorry for being so anxious.

09:50.807 --> 09:53.680
We'll just wait it out
and then they'll pass on.

09:53.723 --> 09:55.333
Okay?

09:55.377 --> 09:57.205
[inhales deeply]

09:57.248 --> 10:00.687
Scott, I need you
to level with me.

10:00.730 --> 10:03.864
What's in that building
that can bring Josh back?

10:03.907 --> 10:05.430
Okay.

10:05.474 --> 10:07.345
You're familiar with the
concept of time travel, yes?

10:07.389 --> 10:09.870
We're in 10,000 B.C., Scott.

10:09.913 --> 10:11.045
Right.

10:11.088 --> 10:12.437
Well, apparently,

10:12.481 --> 10:14.352
there is a room in
that building with a portal

10:14.396 --> 10:17.660
and it can connect
to the future.

10:17.704 --> 10:20.271
You're telling me that
they can control time travel?

10:20.315 --> 10:23.666
That's what Aldridge says,
and I believe her.

10:23.710 --> 10:26.060
She's one of the scientists
that built that place.

10:26.103 --> 10:28.062
They call it the Lazarus.

10:28.105 --> 10:30.238
It's kind of cool.

10:30.281 --> 10:32.414
In a sinister way.

10:32.457 --> 10:35.286
[rustling and twigs cracking]

10:35.330 --> 10:37.637
<i>♪</i>

10:37.680 --> 10:40.335
Aldridge.

10:40.378 --> 10:42.250
It's good to see you, Gavin.

10:42.293 --> 10:44.252
You and I have a lot
to talk about.

10:44.295 --> 10:47.037
<i>♪</i>

10:47.081 --> 10:48.865
- Lucas!
- Hey.

10:48.909 --> 10:50.432
Levi says he wants
everyone back in the clearing

10:50.475 --> 10:51.694
till the fog passes.

10:51.738 --> 10:54.131
- I just need a minute.
- Why?

10:54.175 --> 10:55.611
What are you looking for?

10:55.655 --> 10:58.266
That ginormous field of weed
Scott was talking about.

10:58.309 --> 10:59.615
I thought you
said he was lying.

10:59.659 --> 11:03.097
Yeah I did, and he is.
And I'm gonna prove it.

11:03.140 --> 11:07.014
Well, I can't see anything,
which is Levi's point.

11:07.057 --> 11:08.668
Come on, let's go back.

11:08.711 --> 11:11.322
No matter how much we try
to help the Sky People...

11:11.366 --> 11:12.889
Over there.

11:12.933 --> 11:16.153
They come into our home
and disrespect us.

11:16.197 --> 11:17.720
We will no longer stand for it.

11:17.764 --> 11:19.156
I think they're
from Paara's village.

11:19.200 --> 11:20.723
Our village has been wronged,

11:20.767 --> 11:22.943
but they will learn
to never cross us again.

11:22.986 --> 11:26.424
A price must be paid!

11:26.468 --> 11:28.775
Today!
[all grunt]

11:28.818 --> 11:31.473
I told you we shouldn't
have taken their food.

11:31.516 --> 11:33.736
Okay, uh, come on.

11:33.780 --> 11:36.260
<i>[ominous music]</i>

11:36.304 --> 11:39.699
[birds calling]

11:39.742 --> 11:41.483
Sam!
Hey, hey!

11:41.526 --> 11:43.659
We got a problem.
- What's wrong?

11:43.703 --> 11:44.965
We were out in the woods
about a mile away

11:45.008 --> 11:47.141
and we saw a bunch of warriors
from the village.

11:47.184 --> 11:48.751
There are ten of them
at least.

11:48.795 --> 11:52.015
All armed, ready for a fight.
They're coming for us.

11:52.059 --> 11:54.322
This is exactly
what we told you would happen.

11:54.365 --> 11:55.671
Yeah, well I didn't
see anyone complaining

11:55.715 --> 11:57.281
when they were
eating their breakfast.

11:57.325 --> 11:58.674
Hey, why don't we skip the
arguing and figure out a plan?

11:58.718 --> 11:59.849
We need to hide!

11:59.893 --> 12:01.416
Hide?

12:01.459 --> 12:02.373
How are we going
to find a place to hide if

12:02.417 --> 12:04.680
we can't see where we're going?

12:04.724 --> 12:06.987
He's right,
we're not going anywhere.

12:07.030 --> 12:08.597
We're trapped.

12:08.640 --> 12:12.949
There's only one option.
We'll have to defend ourselves.

12:17.998 --> 12:19.869
We've got a gun
with no bullets,

12:19.913 --> 12:20.870
a few baseball bats,
and some flares.

12:20.914 --> 12:22.306
We can't defend ourselves
with that.

12:22.350 --> 12:25.179
Then we think
outside the box.

12:25.222 --> 12:27.355
We need to create
a diversion.

12:27.398 --> 12:28.791
What are you thinking?

12:28.835 --> 12:30.619
Gather up as many clothes
as you can find

12:30.662 --> 12:33.013
and build a big fire.

12:33.056 --> 12:34.841
The fire would
lead them right to us.

12:34.884 --> 12:36.973
That's exactly
what she's hoping for.

12:37.017 --> 12:38.758
Fire, wood, and clothes.
Find as much as you can.

12:38.801 --> 12:41.369
Let's move.
[indistinct chatter]

12:41.412 --> 12:43.806
Hold on. Look.

12:43.850 --> 12:45.155
Hey.

12:45.199 --> 12:48.071
If Paara is behind this,
I can reason with her.

12:48.115 --> 12:51.074
Ty, I'm sorry,
but if she wanted to talk,

12:51.118 --> 12:52.989
then her people wouldn't be on
their way ready to attack us.

12:53.033 --> 12:54.295
We wouldn't be
in this position

12:54.338 --> 12:56.123
if I'd done a better job
of keeping the peace.

12:56.166 --> 12:59.387
I can't just watch this happen
and do nothing.

12:59.430 --> 13:01.824
There's a lot you can do.
We need your help here.

13:01.868 --> 13:03.260
- Sam--
- I know you care for her.

13:03.304 --> 13:06.394
I do.
But she's made her choice.

13:06.437 --> 13:09.136
Can't make everyone happy
all the time.

13:09.179 --> 13:11.573
You need to make a decision.
It's either us or them.

13:11.616 --> 13:14.576
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

13:14.619 --> 13:20.277
<i>♪</i>

13:20.321 --> 13:21.583
I already
got them up to speed

13:21.626 --> 13:23.193
on the whole time travel thing.

13:23.237 --> 13:24.891
I was going to tell
them about the Exiles.

13:24.934 --> 13:26.457
I know you just escaped
from them.

13:26.501 --> 13:28.720
Unfortunately,
we have to go back.

13:28.764 --> 13:31.158
That's our way
into the building.

13:31.201 --> 13:32.550
You're out of your mind.

13:32.594 --> 13:34.335
The Lazarus uses
the black rock from the caves

13:34.378 --> 13:36.424
as a fuel source
to power the portal.

13:36.467 --> 13:38.252
The Exiles are about
to send in another shipment.

13:38.295 --> 13:40.863
And we hijack it.
That's our way in.

13:40.907 --> 13:43.605
Once we're inside,
we get to the top floor,

13:43.648 --> 13:44.867
which is
where the portal room is,

13:44.911 --> 13:46.869
and we're going to access it
with this.

13:46.913 --> 13:48.131
[clinking]

13:48.175 --> 13:49.306
<i>No, there has
to be another way.</i>

13:49.350 --> 13:52.048
Oh, believe me,
we gave it a go.

13:52.092 --> 13:55.138
<i>There is an
underground security door</i>

13:55.182 --> 13:57.924
<i>which I thought I could bypass
with my old credentials.</i>

13:57.967 --> 13:59.839
Turns out I was wrong,

13:59.882 --> 14:01.144
so I had to come up
with a new plan,

14:01.188 --> 14:02.667
which is where we are now.

14:02.711 --> 14:05.453
And why not just tell
everyone the truth, Aldridge?

14:05.496 --> 14:06.802
Why all the lies?

14:06.846 --> 14:08.848
What we have to do
is dangerous.

14:08.891 --> 14:10.893
Not everyone needed to come.

14:10.937 --> 14:12.895
I didn't want to put
everyone's lives at risk.

14:12.939 --> 14:14.810
Oh, but it's okay
to put mine in danger?

14:14.854 --> 14:18.466
Gavin,
I didn't have another choice.

14:18.509 --> 14:23.514
You have a role to play in all
of this, which only you can do.

14:23.558 --> 14:25.908
<i>[soft suspenseful music]</i>

14:25.952 --> 14:29.564
Is this about my parents?

14:29.607 --> 14:33.481
Silas told me
that they're still alive.

14:33.524 --> 14:35.483
Yeah.

14:35.526 --> 14:38.268
They are.

14:38.312 --> 14:41.706
I've known your father and
mother for a very long time.

14:41.750 --> 14:44.187
The three of us and Silas,

14:44.231 --> 14:46.755
we're part of the team
that created Lazarus.

14:46.798 --> 14:48.800
You're saying
my parents are--

14:48.844 --> 14:50.193
are scientists?

14:50.237 --> 14:54.502
Yeah, very good ones.

14:54.545 --> 14:56.721
Are they still here?

14:56.765 --> 14:59.028
Who's there?
[rustling]

14:59.072 --> 15:02.075
<i>[ominous music]</i>

15:02.118 --> 15:05.774
<i>♪</i>

15:05.817 --> 15:10.170
Paara?

15:10.213 --> 15:11.040
It's me.

15:11.084 --> 15:14.261
<i>♪</i>

15:14.304 --> 15:16.785
Isiah.

15:16.828 --> 15:19.483
[both chuckle softly]

15:19.527 --> 15:22.399
- Ty told me you had returned.
- Yeah.

15:22.443 --> 15:25.054
I wish we were meeting again
under better circumstances.

15:25.098 --> 15:26.229
A group of my people
are on their way

15:26.273 --> 15:27.578
to attack the clearing.

15:27.622 --> 15:30.320
<i>♪</i>

15:30.364 --> 15:32.018
No, my--my--
my family are there.

15:32.061 --> 15:33.541
No, you can't let them.

15:33.584 --> 15:37.980
It wasn't my decision,
but I'm going to stop them.

15:38.024 --> 15:39.851
- I'm going with you.
- No, no, Gavin!

15:39.895 --> 15:41.462
There's no time!

15:41.505 --> 15:43.725
That shipment could leave
the caves at any minute.

15:43.768 --> 15:44.900
We have to get there right now.

15:44.944 --> 15:46.989
It's the only way
to save your son.

15:47.033 --> 15:52.734
<i>♪</i>

15:52.777 --> 15:53.953
[wood clatters]

15:53.996 --> 15:55.302
Careful!

15:55.345 --> 15:56.868
There are some roots
over there, don't trip.

15:56.912 --> 15:58.609
[indistinct chatter]

15:58.653 --> 16:01.917
[groaning softly]

16:01.961 --> 16:04.050
[wood clatters]
[groaning]

16:04.093 --> 16:07.009
- Ty!
- [panting]

16:07.053 --> 16:08.619
Ty, are you okay?

16:08.663 --> 16:11.405
I'm okay.

16:11.448 --> 16:15.409
Look, you should--
you should take this back.

16:15.452 --> 16:18.020
I'll gather some more.
- Okay. You sure?

16:18.064 --> 16:20.762
- Honestly, I'm fine.
- Okay.

16:20.805 --> 16:25.419
[breathing heavily]

16:25.462 --> 16:29.336
<i>♪</i>

16:29.379 --> 16:30.772
[rustling and twigs cracking]

16:30.815 --> 16:32.034
Hello?

16:32.078 --> 16:34.776
<i>♪</i>

16:34.819 --> 16:36.517
Anthony?

16:36.560 --> 16:39.389
Dr. Coleman?
Is it really you?

16:39.433 --> 16:42.088
[laughter]

16:42.131 --> 16:44.307
How is this even possible?

16:44.351 --> 16:46.614
I-I fell in the sinkhole.
Did you too?

16:46.657 --> 16:47.789
Yeah.

16:47.832 --> 16:49.095
I think the last
time I saw you was--

16:49.138 --> 16:51.793
You were on my couch.
[sighs]

16:51.836 --> 16:55.014
This is unbelievable.
- It's so good to see you!

16:55.057 --> 16:56.406
I can't tell you how many times

16:56.450 --> 16:57.929
I wish
I had a psychiatrist down here.

16:57.973 --> 16:59.453
[laughter]

16:59.496 --> 17:03.065
Hey, how are you feeling,
by the way?

17:03.109 --> 17:05.024
- I'm doing okay.
- Yeah?

17:05.067 --> 17:07.113
Thank you for asking.

17:07.156 --> 17:10.116
But what have you
been doing down here?

17:10.159 --> 17:11.595
How have you survived?

17:11.639 --> 17:13.162
I found a group
of people from La Brea.

17:13.206 --> 17:14.424
I couldn't have
made it without them.

17:14.468 --> 17:17.601
- Where are they?
- I'm not sure.

17:17.645 --> 17:18.863
We were foraging,

17:18.907 --> 17:21.257
then the fog rolled in
and I got separated.

17:21.301 --> 17:22.693
I need to find them.

17:22.737 --> 17:24.130
Can you help me?

17:24.173 --> 17:26.219
Oh, Anthony, look.

17:26.262 --> 17:29.570
I--I would love to,
but I've got friends here too.

17:29.613 --> 17:31.876
They're in danger.

17:31.920 --> 17:33.487
I can't just leave them.

17:33.530 --> 17:36.359
Dr. Coleman, anyone
who's out here is in danger.

17:36.403 --> 17:40.146
Please!
I need you.

17:40.189 --> 17:43.540
<i>[soft suspenseful music]</i>

17:43.584 --> 17:45.803
<i>♪</i>

17:45.847 --> 17:49.720
Okay. I'll help you
find your friends.

17:49.764 --> 17:52.723
[knife scraping]

17:56.336 --> 17:59.121
Izz, listen to me.

17:59.165 --> 18:01.689
I need you to promise me you're
going to stay on this bus.

18:01.732 --> 18:03.125
It's safer here.

18:03.169 --> 18:04.387
But I want to help.

18:04.431 --> 18:06.172
Mom, I told you
I can handle myself.

18:06.215 --> 18:07.260
Izzy, this isn't a debate.

18:07.303 --> 18:08.522
Did you make Josh hide

18:08.565 --> 18:11.568
every time something bad
was about to happen?

18:11.612 --> 18:15.181
You have to stop treating me
different because of my leg.

18:15.224 --> 18:16.573
Izzy, this isn't
about your leg.

18:16.617 --> 18:20.142
[scoffs] Yeah, right.
It's always about my leg.

18:20.186 --> 18:21.839
That's not true.

18:21.883 --> 18:25.408
You know, before my accident,
everything was better.

18:25.452 --> 18:30.065
You and Dad were happy.
We were a happy family.

18:30.109 --> 18:32.415
We both know
it's why you broke up.

18:32.459 --> 18:35.070
Your accident had nothing
to do with that.

18:35.114 --> 18:38.029
- Please don't lie to me.
- I'm not.

18:38.073 --> 18:40.336
There were so many things
we didn't tell you guys about

18:40.380 --> 18:42.208
to protect you.

18:42.251 --> 18:44.514
Believe me!

18:44.558 --> 18:47.735
I made mistakes,
your dad made mistakes.

18:47.778 --> 18:51.042
I know about dad's drinking.
[sniffles]

18:51.086 --> 18:52.392
I know you guys had problems,

18:52.435 --> 18:55.264
but that's not
why you split up.

18:55.308 --> 18:56.787
It was my fault.

18:56.831 --> 19:00.182
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

19:00.226 --> 19:01.314
There were
a lot of things going on

19:01.357 --> 19:02.619
that you didn't know about.

19:02.663 --> 19:06.101
Like what?

19:06.145 --> 19:07.842
They're coming!

19:07.885 --> 19:10.149
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

19:10.192 --> 19:12.194
They're coming.
Is everything set?

19:12.238 --> 19:13.456
Yeah, we're good.

19:13.500 --> 19:15.937
All right,
let's get in position.

19:15.980 --> 19:18.200
<i>♪</i>

19:18.244 --> 19:20.724
I'm not staying here.

19:20.768 --> 19:22.683
Fine.
You stay close to me.

19:22.726 --> 19:25.642
<i>[tense music]</i>

19:25.686 --> 19:32.649
<i>♪</i>

19:33.389 --> 19:35.086
[shouting and war cries]

19:35.130 --> 19:37.001
[snarls]

19:37.045 --> 19:39.613
What the hell?

19:39.656 --> 19:41.136
Now!

19:41.180 --> 19:44.226
[survivors shouting]

19:44.270 --> 19:47.316
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

19:48.622 --> 19:50.450
You're surrounded
and outnumbered.

19:50.493 --> 19:52.365
Drop your weapons and go.

19:52.408 --> 19:53.801
We're not going anywhere.

19:53.844 --> 19:56.107
Joseph!
Stop this!

19:56.151 --> 19:58.936
<i>[tense music]</i>

19:58.980 --> 20:01.983
How could you do this?

20:02.026 --> 20:04.812
Dad's back.

20:04.855 --> 20:08.207
They stole from us.
This can't go unpunished.

20:08.250 --> 20:11.427
I decide the punishment...

20:11.471 --> 20:13.342
just as I'll be deciding yours.

20:13.386 --> 20:16.345
[distant howling]

20:16.389 --> 20:21.742
<i>♪</i>

20:21.785 --> 20:24.832
[wolves snarling]

20:24.875 --> 20:26.921
Oh no.

20:31.012 --> 20:33.319
[wolves snarling]

20:33.362 --> 20:36.844
<i>[tense music]</i>

20:36.887 --> 20:37.888
Mom?

20:37.932 --> 20:39.150
Everybody run for cover!

20:39.194 --> 20:40.848
Come on, let's go!
Go! Go!

20:40.891 --> 20:43.067
[all shouting]
- Come on! Go, go!

20:43.111 --> 20:45.809
[barking and snarling]

20:45.853 --> 20:49.552
<i>♪</i>

20:49.596 --> 20:51.902
Eve!
[wolf barking]

20:51.946 --> 20:53.295
Come on!

20:53.339 --> 20:57.560
Becca!
[Rebecca screaming]

20:57.604 --> 20:59.214
[wolf yelps]

20:59.258 --> 21:01.260
Scott, help!
Scott!

21:01.303 --> 21:03.087
Scott, come on!
- Okay, okay.

21:03.131 --> 21:05.438
Go, go, go, go, go!
[Rebecca groans]

21:05.481 --> 21:06.569
In there! Go!

21:06.613 --> 21:08.919
<i>♪</i>

21:08.963 --> 21:11.618
[barking and snarling]

21:11.661 --> 21:13.707
Go, in the bus!
Come on!

21:13.750 --> 21:16.362
[Joseph groaning]

21:16.405 --> 21:18.233
<i>♪</i>

21:18.277 --> 21:19.626
- Get on the bus.
- Mom?

21:19.669 --> 21:20.714
Go, I'll be right there.

21:20.757 --> 21:22.846
Come on!
Izzy, in here!

21:22.890 --> 21:24.457
Come on!

21:24.500 --> 21:26.502
[Joseph groans]
- Let me help you.

21:26.546 --> 21:29.418
[wolf snarling]

21:29.462 --> 21:30.637
<i>♪</i>

21:30.680 --> 21:32.813
Get up!
[bestial snarling]

21:32.856 --> 21:34.945
[arrow zips]
[wolf whimpers]

21:34.989 --> 21:37.208
<i>♪</i>

21:37.252 --> 21:39.428
- Are you all right?
- Yeah.

21:39.472 --> 21:40.908
Let's get him in here.

21:40.951 --> 21:42.910
[Joseph groans]

21:42.953 --> 21:44.999
[wolf snarling]

21:45.042 --> 21:46.479
Go, go, go!

21:46.522 --> 21:50.004
<i>♪</i>

21:50.047 --> 21:52.833
[distant howling]

21:52.876 --> 21:54.182
That's coming
from the clearing.

21:54.225 --> 21:56.793
We have to go back. Now.

21:56.837 --> 21:59.143
You want to go back there?
No.

21:59.187 --> 22:01.668
Hey, hey, hey, hey.
Look at me.

22:01.711 --> 22:02.973
Anthony, look at me.

22:03.017 --> 22:04.845
Remember what we used
to talk about?

22:04.888 --> 22:07.630
Our mind is often
the biggest obstacle.

22:07.674 --> 22:11.286
You can do this, okay?

22:11.330 --> 22:12.200
Okay.

22:12.243 --> 22:14.507
[distant howling]
- Come on.

22:14.550 --> 22:17.074
[Joseph groaning]
- You're gonna be okay.

22:17.118 --> 22:18.728
<i>[ominous music]</i>

22:18.772 --> 22:19.990
Thank you.

22:20.034 --> 22:23.298
[wolves howling]
- Hey.

22:23.342 --> 22:25.431
I'm going to borrow this.
- Why?

22:25.474 --> 22:26.649
'Cause I got
to get to the bus.

22:26.693 --> 22:27.824
Eve--

22:27.868 --> 22:29.217
I know how to shoot
a bow and arrow.

22:29.260 --> 22:30.697
I used to hunt with my dad.
- Izzy is with Sam.

22:30.740 --> 22:35.745
She's going to be okay.
- [sighs] It's just--

22:35.789 --> 22:38.357
What?

22:38.400 --> 22:39.749
She thinks the reason
Gavin and I broke up

22:39.793 --> 22:41.142
is because of her leg.

22:41.185 --> 22:42.578
She just told me that.

22:42.622 --> 22:44.145
You got to be kidding.

22:44.188 --> 22:47.017
I can't believe she's
been carrying this around.

22:47.061 --> 22:49.411
Why would she never tell me?

22:49.455 --> 22:53.894
Probably because
she feels guilty.

22:53.937 --> 22:56.287
Have you told her about us?

22:56.331 --> 22:58.812
No, I want to,
but I just--

22:58.855 --> 23:00.727
I don't know how.

23:00.770 --> 23:03.164
When we get out of this,

23:03.207 --> 23:04.861
you have to tell her
the truth--

23:04.905 --> 23:06.036
her and Gavin both.

23:06.080 --> 23:07.342
They deserve
to know what's going on.

23:07.386 --> 23:08.909
I know, I know.
You're right.

23:08.952 --> 23:11.128
[wolves barking and howling]

23:11.172 --> 23:12.869
I gotta get to her.

23:12.913 --> 23:16.133
[bestial snarling]

23:16.177 --> 23:19.267
<i>♪</i>

23:19.310 --> 23:22.444
[wolves snarling and howling]

23:22.488 --> 23:25.360
<i>♪</i>

23:25.404 --> 23:27.362
All right, open the door.

23:27.406 --> 23:29.233
- That's not a good idea.
- Please, Sam.

23:29.277 --> 23:30.626
My mom and my dad
are out there.

23:30.670 --> 23:34.151
So are the wolves.

23:34.195 --> 23:36.023
Okay, listen, listen.
Listen to me.

23:36.066 --> 23:38.025
I haven't been able to protect
the ones I love,

23:38.068 --> 23:40.854
but I damn sure am
going to protect you.

23:40.897 --> 23:43.291
I can't let you go out there.

23:43.334 --> 23:44.945
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

23:44.988 --> 23:47.643
[sobbing]

23:47.687 --> 23:50.385
<i>♪</i>

23:50.429 --> 23:53.214
I can't breathe.
[panicked gasping]

23:53.257 --> 23:55.390
[shushing]
Listen, listen.

23:55.434 --> 23:56.739
[sobbing]

23:56.783 --> 23:59.263
Remember when Aaron
would put us in our room?

23:59.307 --> 24:01.091
What'd we do we were scared?

24:01.135 --> 24:02.571
[sobbing and gasping]

24:02.615 --> 24:04.007
We'd close our eyes

24:04.051 --> 24:06.401
and we'd imagine
we were somewhere else.

24:06.445 --> 24:08.185
Close your eyes.

24:08.229 --> 24:12.276
[sobbing and gasping]

24:12.320 --> 24:14.017
- Are you there?
- [sobbing and gasping]

24:14.061 --> 24:16.542
[softly] Yeah.

24:16.585 --> 24:18.326
That's good, Veronica.

24:18.369 --> 24:22.199
- [shakily taking deep breaths]
- That's good. Okay.

24:22.243 --> 24:25.551
Just hang in there.
Hang in there.

24:25.594 --> 24:28.510
Don't worry.
I'm a fast healer.

24:28.554 --> 24:30.425
Scott can attest.

24:30.469 --> 24:33.080
She's fairly incredible
that way.

24:33.123 --> 24:35.778
- Hey, Aldridge?
- Mm-hmm?

24:35.822 --> 24:39.869
You saved my life back there.
Thank you.

24:39.913 --> 24:42.568
It's the least I could do.

24:42.611 --> 24:43.917
You need to know that

24:43.960 --> 24:47.616
I did not want to involve you
in any of this.

24:47.660 --> 24:50.924
But we don't always get
to choose our own path.

24:50.967 --> 24:53.448
Sometimes it's chosen for us.

24:53.492 --> 24:57.278
[wolf barking and snarling]

24:57.321 --> 25:00.542
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

25:00.586 --> 25:02.805
Gavin?
- Mm-hmm?

25:02.849 --> 25:06.809
Go help your family.

25:06.853 --> 25:11.945
Okay.

25:11.988 --> 25:13.294
<i>♪</i>

25:13.337 --> 25:16.123
<i>[ominous music]</i>

25:16.166 --> 25:18.821
[wolf sniffing]

25:18.865 --> 25:22.042
<i>♪</i>

25:22.085 --> 25:23.957
[approaching footsteps]

25:24.000 --> 25:26.960
[wolves snarling]

25:27.003 --> 25:32.182
<i>♪</i>

25:32.226 --> 25:34.271
[loud thumping]

25:34.315 --> 25:35.664
- Uh-oh.
- What was that?

25:35.708 --> 25:36.665
[wolves snarling]

25:36.709 --> 25:38.188
They're on the roof.

25:38.232 --> 25:41.104
[claws tapping and scratching]

25:41.148 --> 25:46.196
<i>♪</i>

25:46.240 --> 25:49.765
[metallic rattling]

25:50.984 --> 25:53.552
[wolves snarling and barking]

25:53.595 --> 25:57.164
What the hell are they doing?

25:57.207 --> 25:59.601
They're trying to get inside.

25:59.645 --> 26:03.213
<i>♪</i>

26:03.257 --> 26:06.565
[wolves howling]

26:10.525 --> 26:13.615
[indistinct chatter]

26:13.659 --> 26:16.618
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

26:16.662 --> 26:17.750
<i>♪</i>

26:17.793 --> 26:19.578
Dr. Clark?

26:19.621 --> 26:20.927
Yes?

26:20.970 --> 26:22.015
Sorry to bother you,

26:22.058 --> 26:23.146
but I'm a friend
of Franklin Marsh.

26:23.190 --> 26:25.801
He said you might be able
to help me.

26:25.845 --> 26:27.629
Perhaps it's better
if you find Dr. Clark

26:27.673 --> 26:28.978
during her office hours.

26:29.022 --> 26:30.327
A sinkhole is going
to open in the ocean

26:30.371 --> 26:31.546
and cause a tidal wave.

26:31.590 --> 26:32.634
Please, you have to listen!

26:32.678 --> 26:34.114
I've been over this
with Franklin.

26:34.157 --> 26:36.943
But I have something new
to show you.

26:36.986 --> 26:38.466
I know this sounds crazy,

26:38.509 --> 26:41.861
but these pictures were taken
in the year 10,000 B.C.

26:41.904 --> 26:46.343
That's a saber-toothed tiger.
It's real.

26:46.387 --> 26:50.652
I got there through one
of the sinkholes.

26:50.696 --> 26:52.698
Granted,
the camera's a nice touch,

26:52.741 --> 26:54.961
but it's obviously
some Hollywood prop.

26:55.004 --> 26:57.267
[scoffs]
And those photos? Come on.

26:57.311 --> 26:58.791
The Soviets have been
making more convincing fakes

26:58.834 --> 27:00.183
for years.

27:00.227 --> 27:03.752
Dr. Clark, I'm risking
everything to be here.

27:03.796 --> 27:05.667
There's a way for me
to get back to my family

27:05.711 --> 27:07.103
which could go away any minute,

27:07.147 --> 27:11.107
but I am here
because I believe Franklin.

27:11.151 --> 27:13.893
Please, you need to listen.

27:13.936 --> 27:17.505
I'm sorry,
but I'm late for a meeting.

27:17.548 --> 27:24.381
<i>♪</i>

27:27.297 --> 27:30.213
[whispering]
Listen, I believe you.

27:30.257 --> 27:31.345
Come with me.

27:31.388 --> 27:32.955
There's something
I need to show you.

27:32.999 --> 27:34.957
Well, I'm not the only one
that's interested.

27:35.001 --> 27:38.004
I need to bring my friend too.

27:38.047 --> 27:41.921
[snarling and thumping]

27:41.964 --> 27:44.880
<i>[tense music]</i>

27:44.924 --> 27:46.752
<i>♪</i>

27:46.795 --> 27:48.710
Ella, you need
to know the truth.

27:48.754 --> 27:50.712
[growling continuing]

27:50.756 --> 27:52.018
I've been avoiding you because

27:52.061 --> 27:55.456
I don't
deserve your friendship.

27:55.499 --> 27:57.588
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

27:57.632 --> 27:59.765
<i>♪</i>

27:59.808 --> 28:02.202
When Aaron took you,

28:02.245 --> 28:06.772
I saw you first
outside the church.

28:06.815 --> 28:10.906
You were alone,
and I pointed you out.

28:10.950 --> 28:13.561
<i>♪</i>

28:13.604 --> 28:17.391
I--I chose you.

28:17.434 --> 28:21.308
<i>♪</i>

28:21.351 --> 28:24.572
[sobbing]
And I'm--I'm so sorry.

28:24.615 --> 28:26.443
<i>♪</i>

28:26.487 --> 28:27.923
[sobs softly]

28:27.967 --> 28:29.751
<i>♪</i>

28:29.795 --> 28:32.580
I know you.

28:32.623 --> 28:36.236
You're a victim too.

28:36.279 --> 28:40.849
And I know
you're not a bad person.

28:40.893 --> 28:44.592
<i>♪</i>

28:44.635 --> 28:46.899
I forgive you.

28:46.942 --> 28:49.815
[sobbing quietly]

28:49.858 --> 28:51.338
<i>♪</i>

28:51.381 --> 28:54.907
[snarling intensifying]
- [gasps]

28:54.950 --> 28:56.778
[wolves barking and snarling]

28:56.822 --> 28:58.737
Everyone stay calm!

28:58.780 --> 29:02.044
<i>[tense music]</i>

29:02.088 --> 29:03.785
Thought
you could use some help.

29:03.829 --> 29:07.920
Oh man, those wolves
are literally eating that bus.

29:07.963 --> 29:10.009
Can't possibly taste good.

29:10.052 --> 29:12.620
We shouldn't be here, come on--
- [shushes]

29:12.663 --> 29:15.884
[thunder rumbles]

29:15.928 --> 29:17.451
I have an idea.

29:17.494 --> 29:20.628
[snarling continuing]

29:20.671 --> 29:27.809
<i>♪</i>

29:29.768 --> 29:31.900
Gavin.

29:31.944 --> 29:34.120
We have to get to the bus.
Izzy's there.

29:34.163 --> 29:36.078
Apparently Gavin has a plan.

29:36.122 --> 29:37.819
We still have those rocks
from the cave?

29:37.863 --> 29:39.429
Yeah.
What are you thinking?

29:39.473 --> 29:43.129
Those rocks
are a fuel source.

29:43.172 --> 29:46.480
I'm gonna need your help.
- Okay.

29:46.523 --> 29:48.961
[wolves snarling]

29:49.004 --> 29:51.833
- Whoa, whoa. Sam?
- What are we gonna do?

29:51.877 --> 29:54.488
<i>[intense dramatic music]</i>

29:54.531 --> 29:55.924
<i>♪</i>

29:55.968 --> 29:56.969
It's okay.

29:57.012 --> 29:58.622
<i>♪</i>

29:58.666 --> 30:00.537
[wolves yelping]

30:00.581 --> 30:03.845
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

30:03.889 --> 30:05.847
Okay.

30:05.891 --> 30:07.240
[exhales deeply]

30:09.590 --> 30:11.026
[all screaming]

30:11.070 --> 30:12.941
Get away from the window!
Get away from the window!

30:12.985 --> 30:14.029
<i>[intense dramatic music]</i>

30:14.073 --> 30:15.030
We're okay.

30:15.074 --> 30:16.466
[wolf snarls]

30:16.510 --> 30:19.078
One more good shot
and that breaks.

30:19.121 --> 30:22.124
[thumping and rattling]

30:22.168 --> 30:23.691
- Dad!
- Everyone get down!

30:23.734 --> 30:25.345
Go! Get down!

30:25.388 --> 30:27.913
<i>♪</i>

30:27.956 --> 30:30.219
Where's Mom?

30:30.524 --> 30:33.440
[bowstring creaks]

30:33.483 --> 30:34.745
<i>♪</i>

30:34.789 --> 30:38.227
[whispers] Ready?

30:43.058 --> 30:45.974
<i>[tense music]</i>

30:46.018 --> 30:50.065
<i>♪</i>

30:54.243 --> 30:57.551
[all panting]

30:57.594 --> 30:58.726
Are they gone?

30:58.769 --> 31:02.208
[wolves whimpering]

31:02.251 --> 31:03.731
Mom did it.

31:03.774 --> 31:05.907
We're safe.
We're safe!

31:05.951 --> 31:08.997
<i>[swelling dramatic music]</i>

31:09.041 --> 31:15.961
<i>♪</i>

31:17.310 --> 31:20.443
[fire crackling]

31:22.010 --> 31:24.926
Sam.
How's Aldridge doing?

31:24.970 --> 31:27.668
She lost a lot of blood.
Next few hours are critical.

31:27.711 --> 31:29.626
If there's
anything we can do.

31:29.670 --> 31:31.759
You've already helped enough, Paara.

31:31.802 --> 31:34.588
Thank you for everything.

31:34.631 --> 31:37.634
I know
we've had our differences,

31:37.678 --> 31:39.506
but we're hoping
we can move past that now.

31:39.549 --> 31:42.901
I couldn't agree more.

31:42.944 --> 31:45.729
Your wife saved Joseph's life.

31:45.773 --> 31:47.775
For that, we are grateful.

31:47.818 --> 31:50.256
And you must come
visit your home sometime.

31:50.299 --> 31:51.431
You've been missed.

31:51.474 --> 31:53.302
I'd like that.

31:53.346 --> 31:57.959
<i>♪</i>

31:58.003 --> 31:59.004
Okay.

31:59.047 --> 32:00.744
<i>♪</i>

32:00.788 --> 32:02.746
Hey, Izz?

32:02.790 --> 32:05.488
Can I talk to you for a second?

32:05.532 --> 32:08.274
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

32:08.317 --> 32:10.537
[sighs]

32:10.580 --> 32:12.756
I need you to trust me
when I tell you

32:12.800 --> 32:14.802
that your leg
had nothing to do

32:14.845 --> 32:16.586
with your father and I
separating, okay?

32:16.630 --> 32:17.805
No, we don't have
to talk about it.

32:17.848 --> 32:19.241
No, we do have
to talk about it.

32:19.285 --> 32:22.984
I can't have you believing
something that isn't true.

32:23.028 --> 32:24.377
[sighs]

32:24.420 --> 32:26.466
Do you remember
how hard it was?

32:26.509 --> 32:30.165
Your dad's visions,
his drinking?

32:30.209 --> 32:32.080
And I was--

32:32.124 --> 32:36.867
I was so alone
and I was so scared.

32:36.911 --> 32:38.434
[sighs]

32:38.478 --> 32:41.698
And Levi,

32:41.742 --> 32:44.440
he was there for me.

32:44.484 --> 32:46.529
<i>♪</i>

32:46.573 --> 32:50.142
He helped me through it and--

32:50.185 --> 32:53.232
uh...

32:53.275 --> 32:55.234
things just kind of happened.

32:55.277 --> 32:58.454
<i>♪</i>

32:58.498 --> 33:00.326
[exhales deeply]
Oh, my God.

33:00.369 --> 33:01.849
That's why you broke up.

33:01.892 --> 33:03.242
Um, that's part of it.

33:03.285 --> 33:07.159
But things with your dad and I,
they were broken.

33:07.202 --> 33:09.596
<i>♪</i>

33:09.639 --> 33:14.035
I love your father
and I love our family.

33:14.079 --> 33:17.647
<i>♪</i>

33:17.691 --> 33:22.043
But...

33:22.087 --> 33:24.437
I love Levi.

33:24.480 --> 33:27.353
I still do.

33:27.396 --> 33:29.007
<i>♪</i>

33:29.050 --> 33:32.488
You angry?

33:32.532 --> 33:34.055
[sighs]

33:34.099 --> 33:38.146
A little bit.

33:38.190 --> 33:39.626
<i>♪</i>

33:39.669 --> 33:41.541
Just--

33:41.584 --> 33:42.890
[scoffs]

33:42.933 --> 33:45.371
I thought that when
we got you and Josh back,

33:45.414 --> 33:46.720
we'd be a family again.

33:46.763 --> 33:48.809
Honey, we're always
going to be a family.

33:48.852 --> 33:50.637
Does Dad know all of this?

33:50.680 --> 33:54.032
Not everything.

33:54.075 --> 33:57.687
When are you
going to tell him?

33:57.731 --> 33:59.211
I don't know.

33:59.254 --> 34:05.739
<i>♪</i>

34:05.782 --> 34:11.005
No matter what happens,
we will always love you.

34:11.049 --> 34:12.528
Okay.

34:12.572 --> 34:19.666
<i>♪</i>

34:20.754 --> 34:24.410
[labored breathing]

34:24.453 --> 34:28.675
Hey, sorry, I need a minute.

34:28.718 --> 34:31.330
[panting]

34:31.373 --> 34:33.984
I should never have
left the clearing.

34:34.028 --> 34:36.509
[groans]

34:36.552 --> 34:38.424
It's a problem I have.

34:38.467 --> 34:39.903
I want to help everyone

34:39.947 --> 34:42.776
and I end up hurting
the people I care about most.

34:42.819 --> 34:44.430
It's happened before.

34:44.473 --> 34:47.128
What do you mean?

34:47.172 --> 34:50.479
Please, sit.

34:50.523 --> 34:54.135
<i>♪</i>

34:54.179 --> 34:59.184
About a year before we got
down here, you called me.

34:59.227 --> 35:02.796
You were in trouble,
needed my help.

35:02.839 --> 35:06.800
Me and my wife, we were, um--

35:06.843 --> 35:09.846
we were going through
a tough time.

35:09.890 --> 35:14.155
She begged me not to go,
but I did.

35:14.199 --> 35:17.158
<i>♪</i>

35:17.202 --> 35:20.422
We never really recovered
from that.

35:20.466 --> 35:22.294
She would always tell me
I never put her first,

35:22.337 --> 35:25.688
and she was right.

35:25.732 --> 35:27.951
- I'm--
- Oh, no, no.

35:27.995 --> 35:30.737
It's--it's just funny how

35:30.780 --> 35:32.608
history has a way
of repeating itself.

35:32.652 --> 35:34.654
Ty?

35:34.697 --> 35:36.612
Paara.

35:36.656 --> 35:37.831
Are you okay?

35:37.874 --> 35:39.659
You're never going
to believe this.

35:39.702 --> 35:42.183
This is an old patient of mine, Anthony.

35:42.227 --> 35:44.229
<i>[ominous music]</i>

35:44.272 --> 35:47.145
Wait, he was--
he was just right here.

35:47.188 --> 35:49.495
<i>[soft downbeat music]</i>

35:49.538 --> 35:51.627
<i>♪</i>

35:51.671 --> 35:52.846
What?

35:52.889 --> 35:55.631
There was no one there, Ty.

35:55.675 --> 36:00.419
You were alone
talking to yourself.

36:00.462 --> 36:02.682
<i>♪</i>

36:02.725 --> 36:03.900
Oh, my God.

36:03.944 --> 36:07.469
<i>♪</i>

36:07.513 --> 36:09.515
Has this happened before?

36:09.558 --> 36:11.691
A hallucination?

36:11.734 --> 36:15.434
<i>♪</i>

36:15.477 --> 36:18.393
Hallucination.

36:18.437 --> 36:21.875
No, it can, um...

36:21.918 --> 36:25.052
it can be caused
by my condition.

36:25.095 --> 36:27.576
Means it's getting worse.

36:27.620 --> 36:30.013
Come on.
Let's get you back.

36:30.057 --> 36:32.886
Hey, Paara, wait.

36:32.929 --> 36:35.932
<i>♪</i>

36:35.976 --> 36:38.935
I've made so many mistakes
in my life.

36:38.979 --> 36:41.503
I don't want to make
another one with you.

36:41.547 --> 36:43.375
I couldn't see
what was important before.

36:43.418 --> 36:45.551
Now I can.

36:45.594 --> 36:48.380
I choose you, Paara--

36:48.423 --> 36:53.167
over the clearing,
over everyone.

36:53.211 --> 36:54.386
Ty--

36:54.429 --> 36:58.433
I don't know how
much time I have left.

36:58.477 --> 37:01.828
But whatever it is,
I want it to be with you.

37:01.871 --> 37:05.310
<i>♪</i>

37:05.353 --> 37:09.401
I never told you this, but...

37:09.444 --> 37:11.751
I was married before.

37:11.794 --> 37:12.926
I didn't think I'd want

37:12.969 --> 37:15.842
to spend my life
with another man...

37:15.885 --> 37:17.539
till I met you.

37:17.583 --> 37:20.760
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

37:20.803 --> 37:24.590
Come back to the village
with me.

37:24.633 --> 37:27.549
I'll take care of you.

37:27.593 --> 37:30.465
<i>[swelling dramatic music]</i>

37:30.509 --> 37:37.472
<i>♪</i>

37:40.170 --> 37:42.608
So what exactly were
you going to show us?

37:42.651 --> 37:44.305
It's just in here.

37:44.349 --> 37:46.394
Okay.

37:49.179 --> 37:50.616
Thank you for bringing them, Mattie.

37:50.659 --> 37:51.965
You can go.

37:52.008 --> 37:53.140
What the hell is going on?

37:53.183 --> 37:55.621
I'll ask the questions.
Who sent you?

37:55.664 --> 37:57.144
What?
No one sent us.

37:57.187 --> 37:59.451
You traveled
from 10,000 B.C. to 1988

37:59.494 --> 38:00.843
just to work
with Franklin Marsh?

38:00.887 --> 38:02.758
I don't think so.

38:02.802 --> 38:05.108
I assume you work for James.
- Who?

38:05.152 --> 38:06.632
I know James is trying
to stop my work,

38:06.675 --> 38:08.460
but I'm not going to let him.

38:08.503 --> 38:09.939
It's too important.

38:09.983 --> 38:11.114
Sorry, lady,
but we have no idea

38:11.158 --> 38:12.681
what you're talking about.

38:12.725 --> 38:14.466
Why did you come to 1988?

38:14.509 --> 38:16.337
We didn't mean to.
That was a mistake.

38:16.381 --> 38:17.817
We needed to bring
a little boy to an aurora

38:17.860 --> 38:18.818
and get him through safely.

38:18.861 --> 38:20.646
<i>He</i> had to get to '88.

38:20.689 --> 38:22.909
And then Silas,
his grandfather,

38:22.952 --> 38:24.302
tried to stop us.

38:24.345 --> 38:27.348
Silas?
What was the boy's name?

38:27.392 --> 38:28.349
Why?

38:28.393 --> 38:29.742
Just tell me.

38:29.785 --> 38:31.874
Isiah.

38:31.918 --> 38:33.093
I--I know this is
going to sound crazy,

38:33.136 --> 38:36.183
but he's actually my dad.

38:36.226 --> 38:38.751
Not yet.
He will be in the future.

38:38.794 --> 38:40.361
Wait.

38:40.405 --> 38:43.669
You know who Isiah is,
don't you?

38:43.712 --> 38:46.454
He's my son.

38:46.498 --> 38:48.674
<i>♪</i>

38:48.717 --> 38:52.895
But--but that would mean--

38:52.939 --> 38:58.553
you're my grandmother.

39:01.077 --> 39:03.123
[wheezing faintly]

39:03.166 --> 39:06.387
- Hey, Rebecca.
- [wheezing faintly]

39:06.431 --> 39:08.868
No, no, no.
Sam, help!

39:08.911 --> 39:10.043
She needs help!

39:10.086 --> 39:11.305
Hey, just stay with me.

39:11.349 --> 39:14.177
[breathlessly] Scott, listen.

39:14.221 --> 39:16.310
I'm sorry I can't be there
to finish what we started.

39:16.354 --> 39:17.616
No--

39:17.659 --> 39:19.661
You're going to get
to where you need to go.

39:19.705 --> 39:20.836
I promise.

39:20.880 --> 39:23.230
You just hang in there, okay?

39:23.273 --> 39:25.537
Rebecca?
Hey, hey, hey, hey.

39:25.580 --> 39:27.582
[weakly] Gavin.

39:27.626 --> 39:32.065
I'm not going to make it,
but you're not alone.

39:32.108 --> 39:35.851
Your mother--
her name is Caroline.

39:35.895 --> 39:38.288
She's in 1988,

39:38.332 --> 39:41.814
but she's coming back
to set things right.

39:41.857 --> 39:44.251
Whoa, whoa, whoa, wait, wait,
what do you mean, coming back?

39:44.294 --> 39:47.297
Why is she in 1988?
Can she--can she help Josh?

39:47.341 --> 39:50.039
Rebecca, hey, hey, hey, hey.
Can she help Josh?

39:50.083 --> 39:51.824
[Rebecca wheezing]

39:51.867 --> 39:53.173
Rebecca?

39:53.216 --> 39:54.653
Hey, hey, hey, hey,
hey, stay with me.

39:54.696 --> 39:56.872
I can't do this without you.
Hey, hey, stay with me.

39:56.916 --> 39:58.221
Hey.

39:58.265 --> 40:01.616
<i>[ominous music]</i>

40:01.660 --> 40:08.623
<i>♪</i>

40:13.628 --> 40:15.238
She's gone.

40:15.282 --> 40:18.198
<i>[The National's "Light Years"]</i>

40:18.241 --> 40:21.767
<i>[somber piano music]</i>

40:21.810 --> 40:28.730
<i>♪</i>

40:31.254 --> 40:36.085
<i>♪ You were waiting outside
for me ♪</i>

40:36.129 --> 40:38.827
<i>♪ In the sun</i>

40:38.871 --> 40:43.484
<i>♪ Laying down
to soak it all in ♪</i>

40:43.528 --> 40:46.531
<i>♪ Before we had to run</i>

40:46.574 --> 40:51.318
<i>♪ Oh, the glory of it all</i>

40:51.361 --> 40:54.408
<i>♪ Was lost on me</i>

40:54.452 --> 40:59.413
<i>♪ Till I saw how hard
it'd be to reach you ♪</i>

40:59.457 --> 41:04.026
<i>♪ And I would always
be light years ♪</i>

41:04.070 --> 41:06.986
<i>♪ Light years away from you</i>

41:07.029 --> 41:08.988
<i>♪</i>

41:09.031 --> 41:15.385
<i>♪ Light years,
light years away from you ♪</i>

41:17.649 --> 41:19.433
[owl hoots]

41:19.477 --> 41:23.176
[sighs] Aldridge
was our way into that building.

41:23.219 --> 41:26.484
What are we going to do now?

41:26.527 --> 41:28.877
We're gonna do
exactly what she wanted.

41:28.921 --> 41:31.053
We're gonna go to the cave,
hijack that shipment,

41:31.097 --> 41:33.839
and deliver it ourselves.

41:33.882 --> 41:35.667
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

41:35.710 --> 41:38.060
And then we're going
to get our kids back.

41:38.104 --> 41:40.846
<i>[dramatic music swelling]</i>

41:40.889 --> 41:47.809
<i>♪</i>
